    "content": "nullReport and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Report and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\n Get Ready to Use Net Zero Cloud\n Determine the Sources to Inventory\n Emissions Factors That Affect Calculations\n Create Your Consumption Records\n Manage Scope 3 Value Chain Data\n Manage Your Carbon Footprint\n Manage Your Water Footprint\n Manage the Annual Emissions Inventory\n Record Locking and Recalculation\n Benchmark Building Energy Intensity Data\n Manage Carbon Footprint Data Gaps\n Set Emissions Targets\n Emissions Forecasting\n Carbon Accounting for Extended Organizational Boundaries\n Carbon Accounting for Partner Community Users\n Engage Suppliers for Emissions Reduction\n Allocate Carbon Credits to Offset Unavoidable Emissions\n Allocate Energy Attribute Certificate Credits to Reduce Scope 2...\n Report Social and Governance Data with Net Zero Cloud\n Generate Disclosures by Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n How to Generate Disclosures Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n Capture Reusable Data Using Document Clause Library\n Author Disclosures by Using OmniScript Forms\n Author Disclosures by Using Microsoft 365 Word\n Author Disclosures by Using OmniScript Forms and Microsoft 365 Word\n Design Document Templates in Microsoft 365 Word\n Einstein Generative AI For ESG Report Generation\n Use Uploaded Documents to Ground Answers\n Search for Answers With Einstein Generative AI (Beta)\n Search for Disclosure Guidance\n Analyze the Answers with Einstein Generative AI\n Create GRI Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Create CDP Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Create SASB Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Create ESRS Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Data Collection\n Improve Decarbonization Strategy with Sustainability Programs\n Data Auditing\n Submit Records for Approval\n Use Net Zero Analytics App\n Use DEI Analytics App\n Report Your Carbon Footprint\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nREPORT AND REDUCE YOUR CARBON FOOTPRINT WITH NET ZERO CLOUD\nEinstein Generative AI For ESG Report Generation\n\nMost companies are expected to file different types of environment, social, and governance (ESG) reports periodically to disclose carbon emissions that they own for their operations. Reports include the company initiatives for reducing carbon emissions. Most of the information in these reports remains consistent, so you can often reuse it between different report types. However, the content is scattered throughout multiple documents, or multiple frameworks.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Net Zero Cloud Growth license and the Einstein for Sales, Einstein for Service, or Einstein for Platform add-on license. Einstein generative AI is available in Lightning Experience.\nTo purchase the Einstein for Sales, Einstein for Service, or Einstein Platform add-on, contact your Salesforce account executive.\n\nUse Einstein generative AI to automate response generation from documents, such as previous year reports, policy documents.\n\nWhen you upload the documents, Einstein Search breaks up the searchable content into tokens. These tokens are stored in a search index. Indexing content helps the search engine to quickly find relevant results when you search.\nIMPORTANT Generative AI supports only PDF files for extraction.\nAsk questions in natural language to get responses. When you search, the search engine breaks up your search terms into tokens. The engine matches the tokens against the index to find matching records, ranking the records by relevance, and returns the results you have access to. Access permissions are based on users' profiles. If an object isn’t available in your user profile, you can’t see results for that object.\nAnalyze a response and provide a score to help you evaluate the validity and correctness of a response.\nShow the accuracy percentage for the selected answer and recommendations to improve the answer.\nUse Uploaded Documents to Ground Answers\nGround the information in the uploaded disclosure reports to create comprehensive records that capture the essential fields and data. Einstein generative AI uses the information to produce accurate, relevant, and contextually appropriate outputs based on your data and use cases allowing for more personalized and trusted responses.\nSearch for Answers With Einstein Generative AI (Beta)\nUse the Einstein generative AI capabilities of the Salesforce Disclosure and Compliance Hub for Microsoft 365 Word add-in to search for disclosures.\nSearch for Disclosure Guidance\nA disclosure question can have multiple related questions and the guidance provided with the question from the disclosure authority describes the expected response for each of them. You can view the guidance associated with the question by drilling down on the question from the add-in. Rich text is supported for guidance text.\nAnalyze the Answers with Einstein Generative AI\nImprove environment, social, and governance (ESG) report accuracy by using the generative AI capabilities of the Salesforce Disclosure and Compliance Hub for Microsoft 365 Word add-in. Generative AI compares the question, guidance for the question, and the response to identify distinct guidelines to evaluate the response. It then compares the answer with the identified guidelines to evaluate the response. Generative AI identifies the shortcomings and provides feedback on how to improve the response. To evaluate the validity and correctness of a response, an accuracy percentage score is shown by considering criteria such as the completeness of the answer and the syntax.\nSEE ALSO\nEinstein Search\nPrompt Builder\nEinstein Generative AI\nAuthor Disclosures by Using Microsoft 365 Word\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
